---
// How It Works Section: 3-step process to get started
---

<section class="how-it-works py-20 sm:py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute bottom-1/4 right-1/4 w-96 h-96 bg-green-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <!-- Section Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">
        Get Started in <span class="neon-text">3 Steps</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        From zero to QR codes in minutes. No complex setup required.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Steps Container -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 md:gap-4">
      <!-- Step 1: Install Rust -->
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Install Rust</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">
          If you don't have Rust installed, grab it from <a href="https://rustup.rs" target="_blank" class="text-green-400 hover:text-green-300 underline">rustup.rs</a>
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block"><code>curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh</code></pre>
      </div>

      <!-- Arrow for desktop -->
      <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center">
        <div class="text-green-500/30 text-3xl">→</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 2: Clone Repository -->
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Clone Repository</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Clone the QR Generator repository and navigate to it.
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block"><code>git clone https://github.com/hemil-59s/qr-generator.git
cd qr-generator</code></pre>
      </div>

      <!-- Arrow for desktop -->
      <div class="hidden md:flex items-center justify-center">
        <div class="text-green-500/30 text-3xl">→</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Step 3: Run Command -->
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Generate QR Code</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-4">
          Run the tool and generate your first QR code instantly.
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block"><code>cargo run -- --text "Hello World" --output qr.png</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Mobile Arrows -->
    <div class="md:hidden flex justify-center items-center gap-4 mt-8 text-green-500/30">
      <span class="text-2xl">↓</span>
      <span class="text-2xl">↓</span>
      <span class="text-2xl">↓</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .step-card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(15, 15, 15, 0.8), rgba(26, 26, 26, 0.5));
    border: 1px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    position: relative;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .step-card:hover {
    border-color: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.5);
    box-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.2);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  .step-number {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 48px;
    height: 48px;
    background: rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.15);
    border: 2px solid rgba(34, 197, 94, 0.4);
    border-radius: 50%;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    color: #22C55E;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .code-block {
    background-color: #0f0f0f;
    border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .code-block code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #22C55E;
    background: none;
    padding: 0;
    border-radius: 0;
  }
</style>
